Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.24,0:49:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anybody here unhappy that you are?\NThere could be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.31,0:49:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be somebody that hates that\Nthey are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.07,0:49:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everybody happy that they they are?\N>> Hey
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.04,0:49:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you start from the beginning,\Nyou're happy all the time. I'm happy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.88,0:50:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am. I'm happy that currently I'm\Nin a physical body and I get to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,experience this plane of existence. And\NI'm happy that finally I'll get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.24,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the body and I won't be confined to this\Nprotoplasmic world. I'll be in another
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension where other exciting\Nadventures are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.68,0:50:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whole uh universe to explore.\NWant what you have instead of craving
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.31,0:50:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what you don't have. So you see that\Nhappiness is an inner decision. Once you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.55,0:50:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,decide to be happy, nobody can do\Nanything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.80,0:50:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One source of happiness is just\Nsatisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.88,0:50:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Satisfaction that you are. I mean I got\Nhere today. Hey, what more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.83,0:50:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. There's certain things you\Nhave to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.92,0:50:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why people just don't like\Nbeing happy too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.48,0:51:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to give up. Poor me. Uh-oh.\NA poor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.00,0:51:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Npoor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.59,0:51:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at everything's wrong.\NPoor me. I don't even have a thumb on
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.80,0:51:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this hand.\NEverybody else has two thumbs. I only
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.04,0:51:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,got one.\NPoor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.96,0:51:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one thumb. God,\Nhe owes me a thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.52,0:51:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,By acceptance and by acceptance we\Neliminate the negatives. How do we
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.07,0:51:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,accept it? We choose it to be that way.\NI choose instead of craving and desiring
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.20,0:52:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and wandering. So you stop grasping for\Nhappiness. You see that ha happiness is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.68,0:52:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,completely within yourself.\NStop rejecting the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.20,0:52:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,outside yourself because then you're\Ngoing to want to desire it. You got to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.83,0:52:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,get it. You're not going to be happy\Nunless you have something.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.35,0:52:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a miserable state. You can\Nremember when you're a kid that your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.83,0:52:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness depended on having certain\Nclothes to wear to school or
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.68,0:52:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was a kid, my mother used to make\Nwhen it was raining out, she would make
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.28,0:52:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,me wear rubbers to school.\NWell, if you're a 12-year-old boy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.07,0:52:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,wearing rubbers to school.\NSo, on the way to school, I would dart
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.16,0:52:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the bush, take my rubbers off,\Nhide them under the bush, and go to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.07,0:52:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,school and then get my rubbers on the\Nway back home again.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.00,0:52:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You imagine a what 11 or 12 year old boy\Nand you arrive in school with rubbers
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.00,0:53:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on.\NMoment baby
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.04,0:53:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,put rubbers on your life as hell.\NSo happiness is hiding your rubbers in a
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.64,0:53:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,shrub.\NYou can put them on on the way home from
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.20,0:53:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,school.\NOf course, a smart mother says, "How'd
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.28,0:53:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your shoes get wet with your rubbers\Non?"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.59,0:53:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I shouldn't tell that to mothers.\NNever check that out. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.64,0:53:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the kid said he wore his rubs to school.\NBelieve him. There's lots of better
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.04,0:53:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,things, lots of things that it's better\Nnot get too much involved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.80,0:53:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. 101 ways we got to keep moving\Nnow.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.80,0:54:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?\NSurrender your cravings to God. What if
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.40,0:54:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't let go of a craving? You have\Nto have a new Cadillac to be happy. You
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.59,0:54:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,have to have a new car. You have to have\Nsomething. You have to surrender all
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.16,0:54:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,cravings to God. So this is a more\Nspiritually evolved person.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.96,0:54:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It says in which the love of God becomes\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.55,0:54:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the priority.\NWould I rather crave this thing and be
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.55,0:54:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,unhappy or be thankful for my existence?\NSo prayer now the spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.28,0:54:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then increases the chances of happiness.\NSurrender all cravings to God and you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.40,0:54:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do it in the form of a prayer.\NDear God, I seem to be the victim of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.00,0:54:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this insatiable craving.\NPistachio and cream cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.52,0:55:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes this work is is the\Nwillingness to let it go. What makes
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.00,0:55:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this work is not that God says, "Gee,\Nyou sure are a swell person. Here's your
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.48,0:55:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pistachio ice cream."\Nis your willingness to surrender it to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.04,0:55:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God. It's the surrender. The happiness\Nis in the willingness. I say to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.48,0:55:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,could you surrender this to God? Yes, I\Ncould. That's the beginning of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.24,0:55:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,right there.\NThen the next step is merely would.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.55,0:55:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First step is could you? People say no,\NI couldn't let that go. I say, well, if
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.68,0:55:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I hold a loaded gun to your head and if\Nyou don't, I'm going to blow your brains
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.35,0:55:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out. Could you let it go? Yes, I could.\NSo, realize that it isn't that you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.96,0:55:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,can't, it's just you won't. You can let\Ngo anything that you want to. Now, is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.16,0:55:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody here stuck in something they\Nwould like me to help them out with?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.35,0:56:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happen to have a loaded\NI'll give you a little help.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.72,0:56:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your head under my coat here.\Nboy sure gave up in a hurry, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.52,0:56:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the willingness to\Nsurrender all cravings to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.55,0:56:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh there's a certain hard to describe\Nis independent of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.11,0:56:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So is a certain attitude like\NMaurice Shiovalier
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.44,0:56:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is avi\Nand if you lost all your money today I
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.40,0:56:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,say why are you happy? I'm happy because\NI lost all my money today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.92,0:56:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So happiness is also a certain style\Nand if you want to make it more
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.76,0:57:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,attractive realize it is really a\Nsuperior style.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.59,0:57:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Only peasants are unhappy.\NOnly dumb peasants are unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.48,0:57:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When asked how he felt about being 77,\NMaurice Shiovalier said, "Considering
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.92,0:57:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the alternative, very good indeed."\NAnd at 82 I have to express the same
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.48,0:57:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sentiment.\NIs then a dec part of a decision
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.52,0:57:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a certain attitude towards life\Ntowards is it really an existential
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.72,0:58:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,position\Nof being happy and grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.28,0:58:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoying it.\NSo if you get to be a dog, you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.79,0:58:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,certain joy to be. You go.\NIf you have a kitty, you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.92,0:58:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're horse, you go pop.\NWhat do you Whatever you are. If you're
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.52,0:58:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a squirrel, you get the\Nyou're as certain as you want to be in
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.72,0:58:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever\Nuh expression your life is expressing
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.72,0:58:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,itself right now. Uh being a human.\NWell, that's an exciting trip. Being a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.59,0:58:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,human, I think being a human is\Nextremely exciting. Don't you think it's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.83,0:58:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting? You never know what's going to\Nhappen. you know any moment
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.88,0:58:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly get a heart attack and fall\Nover.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.83,0:58:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can suddenly win the lottery. I mean\Nwho knows what's going to happen. A
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.88,0:59:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,certain joy of bot life\Nthat is independent of what actually
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.55,0:59:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,happens out there. In other words, you\Ndo you play the game for the sake of the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.92,0:59:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,game, not for the necessity of winning\Nthe game. that the game of life, the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.92,0:59:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the game of life, it comes from\Nplaying the game, not from winning or
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.35,0:59:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,losing. Because in human life, there is\Nno way to win or lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.55,0:59:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to win and no way to\Nlose. There's no winning or losing in
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.52,0:59:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,real human life. Winning and losing is\Nall a fantasy you project onto
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.83,0:59:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NIf you think that's wonderful and you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.68,0:59:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,get it, you say, "Oh, I won."\NIf you've taken vows of poverty, you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.88,0:59:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just lost.\NPlease don't give me a camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.92,0:59:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because then I'll have to tie him up.\NThen I'll have to get food for him. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.11,0:59:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to get a shovel for his poo\Npoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.00,1:00:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do not give me anything. You know\Nindependent this. So this if you look at
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.59,1:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it then so be like shar in which you you\Ncelebrate your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.20,1:00:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Celebrate your own existence. You see,\Nif you came to a deserted island where
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.24,1:00:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there was only human being, just think\Nhow overjoyed they would be to see you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.88,1:00:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,paddle up. Wow. They just get so excited\Nthey wouldn't not to do. They haven't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.35,1:00:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,seen anybody in 20 years and here comes\Nsomebody paddling along.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.35,1:00:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So try to be a source of joy to others.\NThe way to experience
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.07,1:00:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be goodnatured and humorous and\Nlight-hearted and helpful to others. And
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.40,1:00:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are that way to others,\Nthat's what you become.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.88,1:00:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain joy of life is independent of\Nevents.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.72,1:00:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're either happy or unhappy, you\Ncan ask yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.92,1:01:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,within ourself. We have unconsciously\Nthe child, the adult or the parent. So
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.55,1:01:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who is it that is happy or unhappy?\NA lot of times if you become the child
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.28,1:01:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the parent in you will get angry and\Nbecome guilty. Yeah. So is it the child,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.11,1:01:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the adult or the parent in you? The\Nparent is the your conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.24,1:01:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your performance and this is\Nyour inner child.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.68,1:01:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of\Nis that the inner child is still there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.20,1:02:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you happy and skipping?\NYou kick a pill off the sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.07,1:02:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo part of happiness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.88,1:02:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is that your child is still active.\NYour adult is well integrated
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.35,1:02:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have a loving parent. That your\Nconscious your conscience is not brutal
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.88,1:02:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and and negative\Nuh that you have total inner acceptance
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.24,1:02:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of yourself.\NIf you have within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.79,1:02:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a negative parent that is critical of\Nyou all the time, then you that's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.83,1:02:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,something you need to see is going on in\Nyou. See that's the inner parent. I have
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.83,1:02:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,interjected that thinking it's myself.\NThat's your inner parent.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.83,1:03:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you live in fear of it. You're not\Nsupposed to do that. Not supposed to say
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.88,1:03:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that. Don't do this.\NSo you see your inner child is just
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.83,1:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,bubbling over with stuff it wants to do\Nwhich your parent will then scold you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.00,1:03:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for.\NYou can't moon people in public.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.44,1:03:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's our motto for today. You can\Nput that on your mirror at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.88,1:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot moon people in public. It's a\Ngood reminder. You know, can't moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.00,1:03:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your kid wants to moon people.\NYour parent would punish you and so your
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.88,1:04:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,adult has to handle it.\NWe won't moon anybody today, Doc. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.92,1:04:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All the way here. They said you can't\Nmoon anybody on the way to Prescott.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.20,1:04:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.28,1:04:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, differentiating yourself.\NWho is it that is being
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.44,1:04:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfied or frustrated? The source of\Nyour happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.64,1:04:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you should own your child all\Nthe time within yourself. The sense of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.35,1:04:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,humor, the shar\Nmeans you have a child that's feel free
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.88,1:04:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to express itself. As you can tell, my\Nchild gets unruly at times.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.31,1:05:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And my wife, I mean, my adult has to\Na couple weeks ago. Can I tell this
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.35,1:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,story?\N>> Going to see the doctor. Going to see
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.52,1:05:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor.\N>> I went to see my internist. I see him a
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.96,1:05:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,couple times a year. And I came home\Nfrom the internist and I had this
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.59,1:05:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,undershirt and it had a hole in it. She\Nsays, "You didn't wear that shirt to the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.35,1:05:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor's office, did you?"\NSo that was the adult and I was being
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.83,1:05:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the child.\NMy child wanted to wear the shirt with a
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.16,1:05:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hole in it\Nand her parent came up and said, "You
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.48,1:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't wear that shirt to the doctor's\Noffice.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.96,1:05:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What will the doctor think of her as a\Nwife?" You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.52,1:05:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You let your husband wear that shirt to\Nthe doctor's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.31,1:06:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah. That's so funny.\NAll that interaction and the subtleties,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.52,1:06:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the cintillating subtleties of\Nthese interactions
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.52,1:06:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are are whereby comes from. You know,\Nthe fun of that story, the fun of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.07,1:06:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, the fun of her response to\Nit. You know, that's part of the fun of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.20,1:06:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,life is that your wife is upset you wore\Na shirt with a hole in it to the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.44,1:06:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor's office. I mean, it's\Nhysterical. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.83,1:06:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have to also differentiate the\Nactual that which is real from that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.64,1:06:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is merely symbolic.\NMany things this world fights for are
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.96,1:06:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,neither\Npart and parcel of either winning or
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.96,1:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,losing, winning or gain or loss\Nexcept symbolically.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.16,1:06:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is symbolic.\NAnd look how people kill each other and
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.07,1:07:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,do terrible things over things that\Nintrinsically have no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.35,1:07:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But they are symbolic.\NFor symbolic people go to war
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.20,1:07:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for symbolic reasons. They bomb each\Nother.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.48,1:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all symbolic.\NSo symbols bring up something within
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.11,1:07:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ourself. So when we're upset or\Ndepressed or not happy, it may be
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.88,1:07:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the symbolic significance.\NWearing a shirt with a hole in it is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.28,1:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolic\Nof neglect and not caring this and etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.44,1:07:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Symbolic.\NSo many the things that cause us to be
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.35,1:07:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,either happy or unhappy have no\Nintrinsic reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.31,1:07:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because we have superimposed a\Nmeaning and a significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.76,1:08:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the significance of the\NAmerican flag. Instantly you go like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.35,1:08:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this and think of what you feel like if\Nyou see somebody stomping on the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.55,1:08:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,American flag. Just soon kill them. Yep.\NSo our life is not only actual emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.96,1:08:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the child the adult and the parent\Ninside
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.44,1:08:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is it's appealing to the\Narchetypes of the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.88,1:08:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things within us on a symbolic\Nlevel.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.88,1:08:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it symbolize? Not what is it\Nbut what does it symbolize?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.92,1:08:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a lot of money.\NHaving a lot of money
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.96,1:08:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in a lot of parts of the world isn't\Nuseless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.31,1:08:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't got anything to sell you\Nwith it. Your your money doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.71,1:08:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. Other parts of the world\Nwithout money, you're nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.48,1:08:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of money then is so\Nsymbolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.56,1:09:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was some place in the world I\Nvisited. as soon as you go ashore,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.96,1:09:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, they have all kinds of things they\Nwant to sell you on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.75,1:09:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh,\Nso they say $25,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.04,1:09:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,$50,\Nand then when you get to town, you you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.52,1:09:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,really they sell them for 25.\NThey sell these plastic images of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.44,1:09:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,antiques for 25 cents in Egypt, too, I\Nthink it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.31,1:09:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,$50, $50. So, some of the naive\Ntourists, you know, got them down to $40
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.88,1:09:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought they got a terrific bargain.\NYou get downtown in Caron, there they
